ENTRY            30079   20260402   20260528   20260528       3223
SUBENT        30079001   20260402   20260528   20260528       3223
BIB                 16         39
TITLE      Test of statistical theory of nuclear reactions
            at 24 keV
AUTHOR     (A.K.Chaubey, M.L.Sehgal)
INSTITUTE  (3INDMUA)
REFERENCE  (J,PR,152,1055,1966)
REL-REF    (M,30063001,A.K.Chaubey+,J,NP,66,267,1965)
            experimental information and uncertainty information.
EXP-YEAR   (1966)
INC-SOURCE Antimony-Beryllium, 1.7cm diam. * 3.3cm height,
            flux approximately 10**7 neutrons/sec
SAMPLE     Powder, purity better than 99.9%, sample sandwiched
            between 2 cellotapes, perspex ring for fixed geometry
DETECTOR   (GEMUC) end window beta counter
METHOD     (ACTIV) Beta activity measured
MONITOR    (53-I-127(N,G)53-I-128,,SIG)
MONIT-REF  (11399033,R.L.Macklin,J,PR,107,504,1957)
CORRECTION Absence of thermal neutrons determined, influence of
            scattered neutrons of lower than 24 keV energy
            negligible due to geometry, i.e. large room, remote
            location of neutron source from the floor (=1.3 m)
            and no shielding material around the source
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Total uncertainty propagated from:
           - Statistical uncertainty
           (ERR-1) Number of target nuclei (1%)
           (ERR-2) Reproducibility of the geometry (2%)
           (ERR-3) Irradiation time (1%)
           (ERR-4) Detection of gamma-rays and beta-counter
               detection.
STATUS     (TABLE,,A.K.Chaubey+,J,PR,152,1055,1966) Table I
HISTORY    (19691124C) Data compiled into Dastar-1012
           (19691203A) Proof copy sent to author
           (19701130T) Data converted from Dastar into Exfor
           (19761209A) Comments revised. Half-lives put in 'common
           or with 'resid-nuc'.Yag.
           (19770907U) OS. Bib update.
           (20080305A) BIB section updated
           (20110812A) VS. TITLE corrected.
           (20160209U) VS. DECAY-DATA corrected in 003,016,022,026
           (20260402A) VT. Entry revised
ENDBIB              39
